## Section 1: Paper Structure Standard

All Onli academic papers MUST follow this exact structure:

### 1. Title and Attribution Block

```markdown
# Title: [Full Paper Title]

**Author**: Dhryl Anton  
**Tools**: Manus AI, Claude AI  
**Team**: Onli Research Team  
**Organization**: The Onli Corporation

---
```

### 2. Executive Summary

- **Target Audience**: Enterprise Decision-Makers (CFOs, General Counsel, Chief Compliance Officers)
- **Length**: 500-800 words
- **Content**: High-level overview, core principle, key findings, comparative tables (if applicable), bottom-line implications
- **Formatting**: Use "Bottom Line for Enterprise Solutions" for the concluding section
- **Style**: Business-focused, clear, actionable
- **Tables**: Use plain text (PASS/FAIL) instead of emojis

### 3. Abstract

- **Source**: Use the exact, verified abstract provided (do not modify)
- **Length**: 150-250 words
- **Content**: Thesis statement, core framework, key findings, Onli as solution
- **Keywords**: Include 10-15 relevant keywords

### 4. Main Paper Body

- **Minimum Word Count**: 3,000 words (excluding Abstract, Addendum, References)
- **Structure**: Introduction → Evidence/Analysis Sections → Comparative Analysis (Onli) → Conclusion
- **Tone**: Formal, academic, objective, data-driven
- **Citations**: All factual claims must have inline numeric citations [1] [2]
- **Framework**: Build argument around a clear, first-principles framework
- **Comparative Analysis**: Evaluate subject against Onli Protocol using the same framework

### 5. Addendum

Must include these subsections:

- **Source Documentation**: Detailed information on primary sources (accounting standards, regulatory reports, legal texts)
- **Historical Citations**: Full context for historical references (Pacioli, Blackstone, Hohfeld, Coase, etc.)
- **Comprehensive Source Documentation**: Full URLs and publication details for all sources
- **Methodology Notes**: Explanation of the analytical framework
- **Limitations and Future Research**: Transparent discussion of scope and suggestions for further inquiry

### 6. References

- **Format**: Numbered list corresponding to inline citations
- **Completeness**: Each reference must include author, title, publication, year, and URL (if available)
- **Minimum**: 15-30 references from authoritative sources

